nhc_headline: ...DISHEVELED JERRY MAY NOT LAST MUCH LONGER AS A TROPICAL CYCLONE...
summary: ...DISHEVELED JERRY MAY NOT LAST MUCH LONGER AS A TROPICAL CYCLONE... As of 11:00 AM AST Sat Oct 11 the center of Jerry was located near 25.8, -63.2 with movement N at 16 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1005 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 50 mph.
